Hey Ho's! I'm not dead! Just in Boston for a few days.....  a few of you better get a hold of me *cough* LILLY MONSTAH! and a few others who know who they are! Come entertain me so i can minimalize my actural time at the evil nana-monster's house so this can actually be a good trip. 

FYI: as most of you know last trip up here resulted in her stealing like hundreds of dollars worth of club gear (ha remember when i was super cyber boy extradinaire? dat shite is expensive! you know!) out of my suit case and locking it in the basement of her apt building and never ever giving it back. we made amends when she decided to take me to paris for my 21st bday... but still....  ya know.. . this time i totally brought luggage locks! not that I brought any club gear up though.

*brain fart*
could somebody PLEASE remind me what thoose thingies are called errr let me elaborate... there was a website you could go to and i guess download a program or something so you could take a pic and super enlarge it so that when you print it out it comes out in multiple pieces of paper so that when you put them together you get a giant version of the pic.... . omg there is totally an easier way to explain but i'm lacking sleep and i have too do to even think about sleep right now... gym, interview, blah blah and on and on ...


ps: wtf is up with job applications, after asking for  all your past supervisors contacts to use as refferences they ask you to give three references that arnt job related or family related... family related i can  understand but not job related...then um who in the world do they want like your friend's numbers??? im totally confused by that ... ..

also what's up with places asking your favorite ice cream flavor in an interview, i swear i've had 3 places do that already and none of them were ice cream shops .....

I am a very frustrated tristen monstah! I really really need a job badly and have been applying to a zillion restaraunts in NYC....how hard can it be to find a job waiting tables in nyc...APARENTLY VERY HARD! 

Like every restaraunt wants 2years NEW YORK CITY table waiting experiance....not just experiance but nyc experiance ...so despite me having a few years experiance waiting tables I think they just totally ignore my application/resume when they see that I moved here recently. I think tonight I need to write up a faux resume that includes nyc experiance because this is really bad. Like all the money I've saved up is running low and I really don't want to have to move back to maryland. 

Alot of the money went twords classes that I've been taking, my mother seems to think I've partied my money away but really I don't pay for anything when I got clubbing and i make most of the things i wear out clubbing so it's not like i've gone shopping crazy (which is acturally a miracle! ) well except for bootleg sunglasses on canal street but thats not alot of $

I NEED A JOB FAST!

I was totally vomiting emoticons from my eye sockets tonight........

*i could totaly sell that phrase as a song name to some factory created "emo band" to use as a song title...OR if I could sing.... haha we won't go there.


and that's all I'm going to attempt to type about that, everytime I try...LJ creates some sorta rucus especially with this "auto save draft" shite which ends up deleteing my entry I had just spent an hour spiting all my feelings into .... and then multiply that by 3.

Despite the nastyness with ebay customers demanding their items haven't arrived yet (well duh when you pick the 6-8 week boat method to Austrailia, you've gotta be paitient!!!!  This is just tying up my acount and I need to get on there and sell my Madonna ticket yo! Anyone have anybetter ideas? 

Despite all that.... I went to a REALLY REALLY FUN party last night......

With blacklight flooding every corner of this Chelsea art gallery, lighting art by Leo Villareal, and innovative inflatable art installations by AKAirways.com, Disorient and Kostume Kult present a summer fundraiser like no other. Put on your neon and blinkies, your extra creative black tie and glowy wear, and dance to house, breaks and techno from the New York Underground and the Deep Playa.  
  
Music brought to you by:  
> Magic Cookie (Disorient)  
> Mikio (Freek Factory)  
> Orion (Disorient)  
> Stadenco (Festivus)  
> 3L3Tronic - Devo and Bianca  
> Taisun (Festivus)  
> ArrowChrome (BlackKat)  
  
Come early for Martini specials at 9 pm.  
Blacklight sensitive fashion show by PHil's PHads and Caitlin Stolley at 10 pm.  
  
$10 limited advance tickets, $15 at the door in costume, $20 without.  
Please arrive early- space is limited!  
  
Flyer:
www.pbase.com/1969/image/60688708.jpg

Kostume Kult is an underground costume art and street theater group that has big fun while pushing the boundaries of fashion and themed events. Founded in 2001, Kostume Kult recently launched a non-profit sister group, Costume Cultural Society, which is developing educational programs and a new downtown NYC Halloween festival. Information at www.KostumeKult.com & www.CostumeCulture.org .  
  
Disorient is an arts collective that has made its presence felt at the Burning Man festival in Nevada for over 10 years, and has brought a new level of Glam-Tech to the New York underground party scene. With art installations, blinking lights and pumping bass, Disorient has created unique and unforgettable events in raw spaces and established clubs throughout Manhattan and Brooklyn. Information at www.disorient.com.  

Despite all the wonkyness (including my job search and bizaro encounter at TONI & GUY Hair Salon well apparently LOL the stylist thought that I had just had my hair styled at a competeing salon....LOL then went on to say that if I let it grow out for 2 or3 weeks we could deffinetly work something fabulous. he said something about not wanting to "represent another companies work in their show book"  *eyeroll* so it's either wait it out or go some where else ...hmmmm....
he

BUT YEAH DESPITE ALL THAT WONKYNESS.....I met a  nice fellow at the party named Jay, Jay offered me some E for free after we'd been chatting a bit. I said

okie dokie since it  is the one party  favor I realy do enjoy quite a bit but really don't do very much of,r i don't  I don't do half  the partyfavors i use to. ANYWAY we ended up talking for hours all curled up and playing with each others fingers and touching each others skin..it wasnt about sex. it was just so cute and  innocent. He mentioned going to a hotel but I'm glad we changed our minds he's to nice of a person to just use for sex , dont think me or him are ready for serious relationships right now... .but he's a nice guy even though we are very much different. 

thanks for that pill , jay.  Everything now feels a bit like the movie Amelie and has kept me wrapped up in positive feelings today. 

Shite laundry is done gotta go get that and hit the gym, ha! did i tell you my mother has mentioned if she's me any thinner than i am now (137lbs) she's putting me in hospital for anorexia which is CRAZY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! i just make sure I burn the calories I eat at the gym, plus i mean I walk TONS in the city, and I LOVE FOOD!! LOL !!!!!!!

PS: please tell me i'm right, okay so i put one of my madonna tickets on craigslist and I had it listed as 5th row since well im sure it is since first row is row A ...i'm row E..... the way I put it up was I told people to give me their best offer and I would concider it...after telling some how NO to $300  she told me that i had posted it falsely and it's really 10th row that the tour seating is organized  aa , bb, cc, dd., ee ... THEN a,b,c,d,e,   but um that makes no sense ..... errr ANYONE KNOW? I should call either ticket master or madison sq garden.....though i sorta think the girl was just mad iw ouldnt sell her the ticket

Bah I HATE THE NEW YORK CITY TRANSIT SYSTEM AND THE RAIN!!! ALL YOU NYC HO'S KNOW WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT!!!!!

Around 3:30 or 4 yesterday the subway stops like in queens err 20 or 30 somthin street and they keep saying 5 more mintues due to flooding ...after an hour me and everyone else are like fuck this and get off to see if we can catch a bus...problem is most of everyone on the subway doesnt know which bus to take to get where they're going just like me. so I decided aww fuck it I'd try walking home haha after 1 hour of that I was lost then hoped on a random bus which took me to main street in flushing which sounded familiar so then I get there but realize that main st is acturally miles long not just a few blocks like the part i pass daily so i'm in this part that totally is like canal street and it's raining like woah ..... I WAS BEYOND PISSED MY HAIR MODEL  THING AT TONI & GUY SALON WAS AT 6....it was already way past that so i go somewhere i never go ....burger king and order some onion rings and pout for ten minutes then I finaly find a subway station but the only train working is the 7 so I thought great ok i'd take that mess to time square then hop on one of a million trains to forrest hills/continental ave.... well NO TRAINS AT ALL ARE GOING TO QUEENS! they had like busses set up and no one controlling shit and bus drivers not knowing where they were going it was mayhem yo! getting on the people knocked an old lady down and almost stomped each other and on the bus some gehto ho was like "i'll bust yo teeth out yo mouth if you dont open dis window"  and just threatening the bus driver the whole time...it was cwazy.... I FINALY GET HOME AT FUCKING 11:30PM what usually takes maybe 30 minutes took me from 4pm to fucking 11


bahhhhhhh and on top of that they over booked my sewing class at F.I.T. and since i was one of the later people to sign up they put me in a class at a later date like june 25th! i was suppost to start on sunday grrrrr ...i might sign up for a fashion sketch class there  that wasnt too expensive since i'm not likeing the art students league that much and the only reason i'm taking these classes is to get my skills in better shape for when i apply to F.I.T. this fall but I really cant afford all these classes right now but my godparents who i'm staying with keep encouraging it so i'm doing something "productive" with my time and i mean they arnt asking for any money for me staying with them and trust me i've offered a bunch of times.  so i feel sorta obligated... bah i need to find a job i think im going to just tell them i signed up for a week of classes for this week and then just job search because i never have the time AND I HAVENT BEEN OUT TO A PARTY ALL WEEK!!! because by the time i get back i dont have enough time to do everything i like to do before going out (if i dont go to the gym in the am i like going in the evening before going out or i feel i dont know flabby. ) aah well i scored a hawt top at cheap jacks and have some hawt ideas i'm bringing to life right now ...expect photos verry soon . .. !

OUCHIES!!! Don't ever throw your bleach strips on your teeth right after brushing...especially if you might of been a bit too over enthusiastic with the tooth brush and cut your gum a wee bit. OUCH!!! This is the extra strength bleaching system by Rembrandt too so it's extra ouchie! 

I've decided I love the idea of bright bright unnaturally white teeth, but crooked you know well like the lovely teeth I inherited from my Dad's side (Mostly English and some  Irish) I mean they were perfectly straight at one point and I had my "Madonna Space" closed up ... when I got braces back when I was 15. Though I got those awful vanity braces that go on the back of the teeth, and even though they might not show, the stupid wires always came out a bit and would cut the fuck out of my mouth. It got to the point where it got so annoying and I was soooooooo sick of having to go back to the Orthodontist to get the wires fixed and just painful in general that I actually took a pair of pliers and pulled the wires out! FO REAL! Though they were almost done by that point and they probably would have stayed perfectly straight if I would have put my retainer in overnight... but bah! Of course I never kept up. But now for some reason I'm loving my crazy teeth and I'm usually not a fan of the crazy un-natural game show host white toothed look... but lately I'm loving it but only if the teeth aren't perfect. For instance Kate Moss....I love her teeth and their as fugged up as ever, some of her's look like fangs almost.

Happy Mother's Day to the few Mommy Ho's who read this =)
Unfortunetly this Mother's Day is turning out to be like all the other's for me, me trying needing to force my mom to go out for Mother's Day and her not wanting to go anywhere "nice". *eyeroll* 

It was a disaster and ended up being super expensive getting down here too, due to the chinatown bus fucking up ... . I forget if I posted about that....

I showed up early for the chinatown bus to DC and the stupid guy tells me it's been cancled and there's nomore that day and to come back tomarow and then I'm like uh WTF give me my money back then, and he was all like "no english!" ......so then I lugg my stuff over to port authority but it was already like 5 or 6 and the next bus wasn't leaving till 8 or 9 (alot were sold out cause of mothers day) and wouldn't get me to dc till after the metro was closed so I'd be stranded.

SO THEN....I lugg my self over to Penn station and check out the train.... everything is sold out except business class seats on the Aceala (It's a slightly faster train than the normal ones and cuts the time by an hour or a half hour..I forget which.)Cept tickets were like $135/$150  so I had to shell that mess out and then wait till 9PM! What really sucks is there I was waiting in the yucky general seats when I acturally had access to the Aceala Club waiting room where I guess they have internet and free snacks and drinks and stuff... and I didn't see it till I was in line to get on the focking train!!!!! GRRRRRRRR so that plus the lost $20 on the chinatown bus, plus the cab ride from the metro station ($20) because it was so insainely late and my friend ended up not being able to get me cause her car was being wonky (i think her bf just wouldn't lend her the car cause he doesn't like me , i wasn't the nicest to him in high school since he had more that a whee bit of a crush on my gf and now im close friends with his gf) SO LIKE ALMOST $200 TO GET HOME FOR MOTHER'S DAY!!! IT WAS SUPPOST TO BE $20!!!!!! 

I'm throwing up ebay auctions for hair dye shit like crazy to get some extra cash and trying to figure out what the best way of selling this extra madonna ticket is since ebay only lets you sell up to face value and mine is worth SOOOOOOOOOOO much more.

BAH I WANA SLEEP!

Haha I forgot to mention, I was at the Urban Outfitters kind of near Union Sq (err I think I'm having a brain fart on the location) and while waiting in line I totaly looked up and one of the olsen twin ho's were totally leaving the register lol or someone who looked excatley like them (ya know a troll like looking girl in clothes that look like they came from a dumpster but are acturally probably very expensive plus suppa big glasses... okay that sounds like every other girl in NYC cept this looked totally like thoose awfull tabloid photos of them bumming around da nyc... ) well the checkout girl was totally smiling and watching the troll girl leave so i guess it was one of thoose ho's OH LAWD bwhahaha .. if it really was it'd be cwazy funny shite since I was watching Full House on zee tee vee that morning LOL!

I'm not saying I'm grateful for this opurtunity to be up in the NYC for such an extended period but ahhhhhh everything seems to be going wrong on this trip yo! 

I'm in back home in Maryland right now for like half a second, I'm going back later up to NYC later this afternoon. Why? Well 2 days ago I lost my wallet! UGH! This is so stupid, I know I had it when I got on a bus in Queens that night because I keep my subway/bus pass ticket in my wallet but this is when I don't know what happend. All I can figure is I put my wallet on my lap and then it fell on the floor when I got up to get off the bus but I would never do such a stupid thing and I know I wasn't pick pocketed, there were only two other's on the bus. I hoped maybe the bus driver would come across the wallet since I realized like 10  min but nothing came of that. I didn't have cash or anything in there but well I'm really pissed because I had just got a new ID and it was a good photo, now I got a replacement today and I came out looking like a fish in the photo!!! And now I need to wait like 7 days for a new debt card so I guess I need to bring a bunch of cash back up to NYC with me, and that just freaks me out walking around with a lot of cash. 

Hmmm I was at the new Patricia Fields store in the Bowery a couple days ago and she was actualy in the store which I thought was weird. I got to chatting with her and a worker there and asked if they were hiring and was told well I was told "WORK DAT SHIT!" and then to bring in a resume. So I guess I'll see what comes of that, but like I think I'd be better off waiting tables but it'd be more fun working at Pat Fields fo sho! (I totally got the tackyiest most fabulous thing ever there, a sequin encrusted fanny pack bwhahaha!). 

Comming home felt awful I deffinetly wana get back to NYC, basicaly my Mother just kept trying to fight with me and call me a freak (wtf!?) etc ....and when I got home I found she'd been through my entire room ..her excuse was she was "cleaning" but she had gone through old private letters from people that I had saved etc... . gawd I was so Pissed. 

BLEH MORE LATER! Tonight I deffinetly want to get muh drink on, this whole little mini trip home has just made it even more clear that I don't belong here at all, the only good part of comming home was seeing my dog molly. HA! MY Mother even told me I was dirty and smelled LOL! It was beyond crazy especially since I'm a hygene freak. I think it's just because I was ignoreing all her other attempts at trying to fight with me bahhhh. 

Righto time to go throw a movie on and try getting a tiny bit of sleep.

I am 100% wasting time till the rain lets up a bit again so I can head to zee gym. YUCK! So I'm thinking 10vol isn't that bad on the hair and I dont need much lift so I'm gonna try picking some up today at ricky's in Manhatten...then just condition the fuck outta my hair. Maybe I should try getting some weave lol just to make it a tad longer and then have it super choppy ....like platnium and white maybe? but I'd have to find someone with a good hook up cause dis ho can't be spendin hundreds of dollas!

ANYWAY hahaha here's the ONLY Photo I found with me in it and I'm in the background and most of my head is cut off and the photo is mainly of some creepy lookin ho! BUT IT'S CURRENT! Okay let's play WHERE'S DA TRISTEN MONSTAH?!??!

Righto I'm off to de-hair my boy bits then off to da city to see about signing up for some sketch classes at the ...okay I always get this name wrong.... New York Students Art League... I actually don't feel anxious or paranoid or stressed today. How nice. Now to find a part time job and hopefully maybe get muh azz into some sorta other living situation. Cause Flushing Queens just ain't cutting it bitches!!!!!

I'm sucha freak, I still haven't memorized my locker lock number code and the directions you turn the thing to open it so like i keep the little laminated directions under my jogging cap when i'm in the steam room like some crazy ho.

Tonight this woman from the Epilepsy foundation is coming to my house at like 6:30 to meet with my mom and I to discuss possible financial aide for school and other things I might qualify for (due to my seizure disorder). I definitely will be eating my Ativan (anti-anxiety pill) like candy tonight, I hate interviews/meetings. This whole thing seems a bit odd to me, I mean usually you would go to an office or something for the meeting/interview whatever, but apparently they usually come to the people's houses because most people they are dealing with don't drive (due to epilepsy). So yeah I don't know what to expect really, but I've just been cleaning all day like crazy.
 
I feel kind of like I shouldn't even be meeting with this woman because I mean yeah technically I have a seizure disorder but I'm fine if I take my Depekote. I mean I don't feel like I am "disabled" I do all the things your not supposed to do if you have seizure disorders: I drink alcohol, I'm a caffeine freak, I do a lot of cardio work out at the gym, I have a prescription for Dexedrine (which is an amphetamine, supposedly a big no-no for seizure people) ,oh and yeah the prescription is legit from my Dr. So yeah if I can do all this and am fine then I kinda feel like I shouldn't be applying for help you know? But then again if I miss more than 3 or 4 doses of my Depekote I almost definitely have a seizure and end up all busted up. It really scares me because what about when I move out and say my job doesn't have insurance? I mean I NEED Depekote or I'll be having seizures every other day like way before (I mean everyone knew me on a first name basis at the emergency room from me coming in after dislocating my arm during a seizure). Then there's the whole car/driving thing, another good reason for me to be moving to NYC. You don't need a car there, it's just annoying to have one in da NYC most of the time.
 
So yeah I'm gonna see what this lady says, and try to milk it for what it's worth because I sure could use help with funds for school and insurance and whatever else and if they wana help me then why not. Though of course being the air head I can be, I am still not 100% sure of the point of this visit  or what we are trying to accomplish but from the bits and pieces my mother has told me and what I'm looking up online last minute this is what I get.
